description.narrative: Legislative and administrative frameworks, accountability and national capacity are strengthened to plan, budget and prevent and respond to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect., which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable prevention of and response to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect of children.

description.narrative: NCFA, with UNICEF financial and technical support finalized the costing study for the implementation of child rights and juvenile laws in Jordan as a mandatory requirement for Jordanian legislators to review and approve both laws. An advocacy workshop was organized with key parliamentarians, heads of institutions, key civil society organizations and medias to increase knowledge and understanding on the results of the costing study and discuss bottlenecks in moving forward with final adoption of the laws. The event resulted with agreement of key actions for NCFA and head of parliamentary legal committee. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:22/12/2021
